LINDE INDONESIA, PT
Employment Opportunity Innovation, Internationality, PerformanceThe Linde Group is the world’s leading gases and engineering company with around 55,000 employees working in more than 100 countries worldwide. In the 2012 financial year, it achieved sales of EUR 13.5 bn. The strategy of The Linde Group is geared towards long-term profitable growth and focuses on the expansion of its international business with forward-looking products and services. Linde acts responsibly towards its shareholders, business partners, employees, society and the environment – in every one of its business areas, regions and locations across the globe. Linde is committed to technologies and products that unite the goals of customer value and sustainable development. PT Linde Indonesia, part of The Linde Group is expanding business aggressively and offering challenges for high potential talents in the following positions:
GAS APPLICATION ENGINEER – JAKARTA BASED
ResponsibilityLead the Manufacturing Industries segment development :Develop technical competence of the Country sales teams in line with agreed priorities Identify key manufacturing growth segments Propose and coordinate specific campaignsMonitor the major business win / losses Establish and maintain an extensive network with the most relevant OEMs, Industry Associations , Key Accounts, etc. Collaborate with the Country sales force in the area of competence Contact current and prospective customers to present Linde gas applications portfolio. Define the best customer technical solutionRun gas applications / test trials at customer site (when required) Manage the interface with regional/country teams (where necessary)Prepare commercial offers, or in collaboration with the Country M&PG sales team RequirementEngineering degree from reputable university with Mechanical backgroundMIG / TIG welding experience with additional knowledge of Laser Cutting would be an advantageHaving work experience with an Engineering company is essential. Customer orientated with excellent communications skills   Strong in mechanical calculation and hands on of machineryAnalytical thinking and concern for detailsHaving excellence negotiation and influencing skills Candidate shall apply on the latest of two weeks throughE-mail :
